name: searching flights

testSteps.description: Example 1: {originCity=San Diego, destinationCity=San Francisco, departureDate=February 28, arrivalDate=March 21}

children.description: Given flight search page of kayak web site
And name of the cities and dates
When user enters the  "San Diego" and "San Francisco" cities
And selects "February 28" and "March 21" for departure and arrivals:
* selects "San Diego" and "San Francisco" one airport from available options
Then user should be able to see the search result that contains entered cities "San Diego" "San Francisco"

userStory.narrative:
As a user,
    I should be able to search flight
        so that I can find multiple flight results that first one shows my entered results.

dataTable.scenarioOutline:
Given flight search page of kayak web site
And name of the cities and dates
When user enters the  "<originCity>" and "<destinationCity>" cities
And chooses nearby airports
And selects "<departureDate>" and "<arrivalDate>" for departure and arrivals:
* clicks on search button
* selects "<originCity>" and "<destinationCity>" one airport from available options
Then user should be able to see the search result that contains entered cities "<originCity>" "<destinationCity>"
